      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm looking at this NDA my new contractor sent over and it's a bit long. can u just summarize the main parts for me? specifically what they consider confidential and how long the agreement lasts. thanks.\n\n[Text of NDA:\nNON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement (the \"Agreement\") is entered into as of October 14, 2023, by and between TechFlow Solutions LLC (\"Disclosing Party\") and Jordan Miller (\"Receiving Party\").\n1. Definition of Confidential Information. \"Confidential Information\" shall mean all non-public, proprietary, or sensitive information, whether oral, written, or electronic, disclosed by Disclosing Party to Receiving Party, including but not limited to business plans, customer lists, software code, and financial projections.\n2. Obligations. Receiving Party agrees to maintain the strict confidentiality of the Information and shall not disclose it to any third party without prior written consent.\n3. Term and Termination. This Agreement shall remain in effect for a period of three (3) years from the date of disclosure, notwithstanding the termination of any underlying business relationship.\n4. Remedies. The parties agree that any breach of this Agreement may cause irreparable harm, entitling the Disclosing Party to seek injunctive relief in addition to any other legal remedies.]",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
